Citation.sAbstract: Liquid liquid (L L), solid liquid (S L), and solid liquid liquid (S L L) equilibrium data for the water ethanol 1-undecanol ternary system have been determined experimentally at (275.15, 278.15, 281.15, 288.15, and 298.15) K and atmospheric pressure. Different shapes of the equilibrium diagrams have been observed depending on the temperature. A region with three phases (S L L) is present in the temperature range between (275.15 and 281.15) K. Above 288.15 K, only a L L region is observed.
Citation.sTitle: Influence of the Temperature on the Liquid Liquid Solid Equilibria of the Water + Ethanol + 1-Undecanol Ternary System

PhaseTransition.sMethodName: Part of LLE-SLE study by chromatography
